INT. THRONE ROOM IN THE CITADEL OF HATRED
The PLAYER stands next to NEYRELLE, before the MEPHISTO in the BLOOD BUBBLE.

As he continues to speak, Neyrelle and the Player exchange a glance. They nod to each other. She steels herself, readying for the challenge.
She touches the membrane and then quickly recoils.
She pulls the DIM SOULSTONE from her pouch.
She marches up to the membrane and plunges the stone deep into it without hesitation.

The Player takes a step back, aghast at the display. 
Mephisto’s essence pulses and roils beneath the membrane as it begins to slowly enter the soulstone.
Neyrelle struggles to hold the stone still. As the ritual progresses, it begins to glow with life, pulsing in time with Mephisto’s heartbeat.
His essence is pulled inwards, shrinking with each pulse.
Both caster and subject struggle, Mephisto in pain and Neyrelle in great exertion. She is helping to birth him.
The ritual nears conclusion. Mephisto speaks, his voice quieter as he is almost fully absorbed into the stone.

The sound of destruction in the distance heralds Lilith’s imminent approach.
Mephisto and his heartbeat decrescendo to silence.
Neyrelle stumbles as the magic dispels. She presses the back of her hand to her head, recovering.
The Player rushes to her side.

Neyrelle holds out the NOW GLOWING SOULSTONE. 
The player shakes their head “No”.

Neyrelle begins to speak, about to protest, but the Player shakes their head and holds up their hand. She lowers hers. 
The stone PULSES BRIGHTLY through her small fingers.
Neyrelle pauses. She understands, but there is pain in the smile she forces. She is much too old for 16.

The player nods.
Neyrelle rushes to open a secret hallway and slips inside. The Player watches her depart. 
They turn around to see LILITH leaning in the frame of the main entrance. She flies towards the Player and lands, causing them to jump away in panic.

Lilith stands to her full height.
She cuts a menacing silhouette against the fires that burn behind her. She's wrought havoc in her father’s kingdom.
She is drenched in blood: both hers, from her open wound, and others’. 
She approaches, trailing it behind her. She is not as regal as we are used to. She is unhinged, run ragged. Scary.
The Player readies their weapon. Lilith keeps what composure she can, but her fury simmers beneath the surface. She stalks forward.
Lilith flourishes her wings, spraying blood with the movement. A fighting stance. Despite her injuries, she is ready to win at any cost.
